Repackaged from Anthropic's official Claude Desktop Linux build **version
`__VERSION__`** into RPM, AppImage, tarball and `.deb` for x86_64 and aarch64.
The only change to the app is two small GNOME-Wayland fixes (Quick Entry hotkey
toggle + its own WM_CLASS); everything else is faithful to upstream.

**What changed in the app:** the build number `__VERSION__` is internal and has
no separate entry, so see Anthropic's official release notes for the actual
changes in the app: https://support.claude.com/en/articles/12138966-release-notes

**Verify** (each RPM carries an embedded GPG signature; `SHA256SUMS.txt` is
signed with the same key, published as `RELEASE-PUBKEY.asc`):

```
gpg --import RELEASE-PUBKEY.asc
gpg --verify SHA256SUMS.txt.asc SHA256SUMS.txt && sha256sum -c SHA256SUMS.txt
```

Installation and the GNOME Wayland Quick Entry hotkey are documented in the
[README](https://github.com/__REPO__#readme).
